Amanda Khoza, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; One man died and another was wounded in two separate stabbings in Margate, on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast, paramedics said on Saturday.Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said that in the early hours of Saturday, paramedics responded to an incident in which a man was found unresponsive by an off-duty paramedic along Marine Drive in Margate.The 25-year-old man had a large laceration to the top of his arm. He was resuscitated and regained a pulse. He started breathing spontaneously and was taken to a hospital in Port Shepstone for further treatment.In a separate incident, Botha said paramedics responded to a stabbing incident on Ridge Road in Margate.They found an 18-year-old man lying on the ground with a stab wound to the chest. He was declared dead at the scene.Authorities are investigating both incidents.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.